item.content:encoded:
Maximus Multiband Maximizer is included with FL Studio Producer Edition and up. It will quickly become one of the most satisfying tools in your mixing and mastering chain. Used sparingly, Maximus will raise the volume of the track without introducing unwanted distortion and ensures that the quieter parts, often lost in the mix, are more easily heard. Bass can be increased and higher frequencies sharpened. Selected elements of a mix, instruments or vocals for example, or complete tracks are given a professionally mastered 'presence'. item.title: FL STUDIO 21.2 | What’s New?
item.dc:creator: Image Line Software
item.description: FL STUDIO 21.2 | We’re excited to release FL Studio 21.2. This major update introduces the highly-anticipated Stem Separation and FL Cloud - a creativity-first collection of services, made exclusively for FL Studio based on customer feedback. Also added are new features and tools for FL Studio, including Audio Clips...
item.content:encoded:
FL STUDIO 21.2 | We’re excited to release FL Studio 21.2. This major update introduces the highly-anticipated Stem Separation and FL Cloud - a creativity-first collection of services, made exclusively for FL Studio based on customer feedback. Also added are new features and tools for FL Studio, including Audio Clips for FL Studio Fruity Edition and Kepler, a new analog-modeling synth. All because we love your Lifetime Free Updates!  

DOWNLOAD FL STUDIO 21 OR BUY FL STUDIO 

(Customers please reapply your license to unlock this release)

WHAT'S NEW

All FL Studio customers get 1 Month of free full-access to FL Cloud. Just open FL Studio 21.2 and click the Sounds Tab in the Browser to get started. 

FL Cloud - Built right inside FL Studio, FL Cloud delivers:

  • Fully-integrated sample library – A vast, ever-growing library of loops and one-shots, including exclusive Artist Packs, with all loops automatically synced to Project tempo.
  • AI-powered mastering – Masters created in seconds, tailored with presets for all major genres and loudness-optimized for all major streaming and download platforms. 
  • Digital distribution – Powered by DistroKid, an unlimited number of tracks can be released to Spotify, Apple Music, and all major digital platforms. 

There are several ways to use FL Cloud:

  • Subscription – Unrestricted, credit-free access to all features. Download any sound at any time without worrying about how many credits they have left, or whether or not they will expire. 
  • Free features –  A curated, credit-free library of loops and one-shots, plus unlimited use of mastering, using a Default genre preset.
  • Credit packs - FL Studio users and trial users can access any sounds from the full library, including Artist Packs, with the purchase of non-expiring credits.

While we believe subscriptions are a great way to provide ongoing content and online services, we would also like to reassure customers, FL Studio will always include Lifetime Free Updates and no one will be forced to use a subscription to use FL Studio. That is our promise to you.

FL Studio

  • Stem Separation – Available for FL Studio Producer Edition and above, splits any song or track into vocals, music, bass, and drums.
  • Kepler (Producer Edition) – A painstaking recreation of an iconic analog synth from the 80s, included in FL Studio Producer Edition and above.
  • Vintage Phaser – All-new engine for Vintage Phaser (included with FL Studio Signature Edition and All Plugins Edition), featuring a Feedback Inversion control.
  • Audio Clips for Fruity Edition – Up to eight Audio Clips available, allowing the addition of vocals and loops, plus, for the first time, complex audio chops and edits. 
  • Colored waveform customization– More detailed visualization of an Audio Clip’s frequency content.

The FL Studio 21.2 update is available now as a free download for all license owners and Trial users. 

To see the full list of changes since 21.1 check the Complete Change Log

Image-Line
item.metadata:description: FL Studio 21.2 featuring Stem Separation and FL Cloud – a new, integrated service with you everything need to create and release your best music. We love YOUR Lifetime Free Updates!

Colored waveforms for better sample management. An extreme chorus plugin, ‘Hyper Chorus’, AI Declipper in Edison and much more. All...
item.content:encoded:
FL STUDIO 21.1 | We're excited to release of FL Studio 21.1. Introducing faster and more creative note editing with scale snapping and custom note tools in the Piano roll. Colored waveforms for better sample management. An extreme chorus plugin, ‘Hyper Chorus’, AI Declipper in Edison and much more. All because we love your Lifetime Free Updates!  

DOWNLOAD FL STUDIO 21 OR BUY FL STUDIO 

(Customers please reapply your license to unlock this release)

WHAT'S NEW?

  • FL Studio:
    • Colored waveforms - General settings option to color code frequency content in audio waveforms. This applies to the Browser, Playlist, Sampler Channel etc.
    • MIDI Control - New 'External sync' mode & improved MIDI master clock stability. This allows FL Studio to 'slave' to an external MIDI Clock so that it plays in time to an external MIDI clock source.
    • Automated updates - Option to automatically download FL Studio updates and apply them at the next restart.
  • Piano roll
    • Snap to Scale - Piano roll option to snap notes to the selected scale on placement or movement. See the note icon on the toolbar.
    • Menu > Tools > Script - Scripts are Python based that allows custom manipulation of Piano roll data. There are several pre-made scripts or you can write your own. Scripting also includes automatic user interface creation. See the Piano roll scripting forum to share and discuss Scripts.
  • New & Updated Plugins
    • Hyper Chorus - Extreme chorus FX plugin, included with Producer Edition and up.
    • Edison Declipper - New and improved AI-based declipping tool. Can restore recordings that have been clipped due to level issues.
    • SliceX - Now resizable by dragging the lower-right corner.

CHANGES

Full list of changes since 21.0.3: Complete Change Log

item.metadata:description: FL Studio 21.1 with Piano roll scale snapping & scripting. Colored waveforms. Hyper Chorus FX & much more. We love YOUR Lifetime Free Updates!

item.title: Novation FLkey 49 and 61 Are Here
item.dc:creator: Image Line Software
item.description: Novation | The ultimate range of MIDI keyboards for making music in FL Studio just got bigger with the FLkey 49 and 61, in addition to the FLkey Mini and 37. Now you can choose a controller that fits your bag, studio or stage. Learn more at Novation What's New?...
item.content:encoded:
Novation | The ultimate range of MIDI keyboards for making music in FL Studio just got bigger with the FLkey 49 and 61, in addition to the FLkey Mini and 37. Now you can choose a controller that fits your bag, studio or stage.

Learn more at Novation 

What's New?

In addition to more keys, the FLkey 49 and 61 add dedicated controls for the Mixer and Channel Rack, giving you hands-on control of volume and pan with eight pots, nine faders, and nine fader buttons for easy mutes and solos. A new Pattern Pad mode, also applicable to FLkey 37, keeps you in the flow by allowing you to select and edit patterns directly from the pads – without needing to reach for your mouse.

Existing owners of FLkey 37 can update to the latest firmware via Components to enable Pattern Pad mode. Open MIDI Options and choose 'Update MIDI scripts' at the bottom of the page.  See the MIDI Scripting forum for full details.

Image-Line

*FLkey is manufactured and distributed by Novation Digital Music Systems.
item.metadata:description: The ultimate range of MIDI keyboards for making music in FL Studio just expanded. Introducing FLkey 61 and 49. More keys more fun!
